flowRoot.flowPara: When the navigation sidebar is hidden, a button is shown in the header bar and the same UI can be accessed through a popover.

When the navigation sidebar is hidden, a button is shown in the header bar. Pressing it shows the panel - when this shown it is overlaid on top of other content rather than moving other UI out of the way. When an item is selected from the sidebar, it automatically hides.
Semi-transparent button is shown when pointer is close to left window egde. Clicking it reveals the navigation panel.
Page popover - document outline on the left, options on the right.
